  <acttitle>Plant Protection Act</acttitle>
  <title>North American Gypsy Moth Eradication Regulation, 2020</title>
  <regnum>81/2020</regnum>
  <change regulation="">
    <changenote eff="April 1, 2021">Regulation BEFORE repealed by BC Reg <amendingreg>102/2021</amendingreg>, effective April 1, 2021.</changenote>
    <reg:regulation index="">
      <reg:regnum>81/2020</reg:regnum>
      <reg:oic>O.C. 170/2020</reg:oic>
      <reg:deposited>April 6, 2020</reg:deposited>
      <reg:acttitle>Plant Protection Act</reg:acttitle>
      <reg:title>North American Gypsy Moth<in:br/> Eradication Regulation, 2020</reg:title>
      <reg:content>
        <bcl:section id="d0e26">
          <bcl:marginalnote>Definitions</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>In this regulation:</bcl:text>
          <bcl:definition id="d0e37">
            <bcl:text>
              <in:term>Btk</in:term> means an insecticide containing Bacillus thuringiensis var. kurstaki as its active ingredient;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:definition>
          <bcl:definition id="d0e55">
            <bcl:text>
              <in:term>buffer zone</in:term> means the area shown in grey surrounding a treatment zone on the map in the Schedule that relates to that treatment zone;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:definition>
          <bcl:definition id="d0e46">
            <bcl:text>
              <in:term>gypsy moth</in:term> means the North American gypsy moth;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:definition>
          <bcl:definition id="d0e58">
            <bcl:text>
              <in:term>treatment zone</in:term> means an area defined in the Schedule by</bcl:text>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d0f51">
              <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>the name of the treatment zone, and</bcl:text>
            </bcl:paragraph>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d0f54">
              <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>a map following the name that shows the area within which treatment may occur with a boundary outlined in heavy black.</bcl:text>
            </bcl:paragraph>
          </bcl:definition>
        </bcl:section>
        <bcl:section id="d0e74">
          <bcl:marginalnote>Powers of inspectors</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
          <bcl:subsection id="d0e78">
            <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>Subject to the limits set out in section 3, an inspector has the following powers:</bcl:text>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d0e126">
              <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>to undertake treatment within a treatment zone by applying Btk, using an aerial or ground spray;</bcl:text>
            </bcl:paragraph>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d0e135">
              <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>to enter on land in a treatment zone to do any of the following:</bcl:text>
              <bcl:subparagraph id="d0e140">
                <bcl:num>i</bcl:num>
                <bcl:text>search for and remove gypsy moth eggs;</bcl:text>
              </bcl:subparagraph>
              <bcl:subparagraph id="d0e153">
                <bcl:num>ii</bcl:num>
                <bcl:text>search for gypsy moths;</bcl:text>
              </bcl:subparagraph>
              <bcl:subparagraph id="d0e162">
                <bcl:num>iii</bcl:num>
                <bcl:text>set or retrieve traps for gypsy moths.</bcl:text>
              </bcl:subparagraph>
            </bcl:paragraph>
          </bcl:subsection>
          <bcl:subsection id="d0e118">
            <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>Nothing in subsection (1) (a) limits an authorization granted under the <in:doc>Integrated Pest Management Act</in:doc> for overspray or drift from treatment to pass into the buffer zone surrounding the treatment zone.</bcl:text>
          </bcl:subsection>
        </bcl:section>
        <bcl:section id="d0e145">
          <bcl:marginalnote>Limits on powers</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
          <bcl:subsection id="d0f117">
            <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>An inspector may exercise powers under section 2 only as follows:</bcl:text>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d0e171">
              <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>Btk may be applied in a treatment zone set out in Column 1 of the following table only during the period set out in Column 2 opposite that treatment zone;</bcl:text>
            </bcl:paragraph>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d0f131">
              <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>no more than 3 treatments may be undertaken during the period authorized under paragraph (a);</bcl:text>
            </bcl:paragraph>
            <bcl:paragraph id="d1e161">
              <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>land in a treatment zone may be entered for a purpose set out in section 2 (1) (b) only during the period set out in Column 3 of the following table opposite that treatment zone.</bcl:text>
            </bcl:paragraph>
          </bcl:subsection>
          <oasis:table style="2" id="d1f131">
            <oasis:tgroup cols="4">
              <oasis:colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" align="center" border="1"/>
              <oasis:colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" align="center" border="1"/>
              <oasis:colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" align="center" border="1"/>
              <oasis:colspec colname="c4" colnum="4" align="center" border="1"/>
              <oasis:tbody>
                <oasis:trow>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c1" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Item</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c2" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Column 1 <in:br/><in:strong>Treatment Zone</in:strong></oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c3" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Column 2 <in:br/><in:strong>Spray Period</in:strong></oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c4" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Column 3 <in:br/><in:strong>Entry Period</in:strong></oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                </oasis:trow>
                <oasis:trow>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c1" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>1</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c2" align="left" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Castlegar Gypsy Moth Treatment Zone </oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c3" align="left" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>April 15, 2020 to June 30, 2020 </oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c4" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>April 15, 2020 to October 30, 2020</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                </oasis:trow>
                <oasis:trow>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c1" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>2</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c2" align="left" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Cowichan Gypsy Moth Treatment Zone</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c3" align="left" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>April 15, 2020 to June 30, 2020</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c4" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>April 15, 2020 to October 30, 2020</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                </oasis:trow>
                <oasis:trow>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c1" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>3</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c2" align="left" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>Surrey Gypsy Moth Treatment Zone</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c3" align="left" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>April 15, 2020 to June 30, 2020</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                  <oasis:entry colname="c4" align="center" valign="top">
                    <oasis:line>April 15, 2020 to October 30, 2020</oasis:line>
                  </oasis:entry>
                </oasis:trow>
              </oasis:tbody>
            </oasis:tgroup>
          </oasis:table>
          <bcl:subsection id="d1e208">
            <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>For the purposes of subsection (1) (b), a treatment may consist of the application of Btk over multiple days if, due to mechanical, meteorological or any other reason, Btk cannot be applied throughout the treatment zone in a single day.</bcl:text>
          </bcl:subsection>
        </bcl:section>
